01:40:34,816 --> 01:40:38,820
-Did the sound frighten you?
-Very much.

1431
01:40:38,987 --> 01:40:41,657
Did you close your eyes?

1432
01:40:43,158 --> 01:40:46,370
At first... until the shooting stopped.
Then I opened them.

1433
01:40:46,662 --> 01:40:50,666
Did you think the men who were shooting
were going to kill everybody in McHale's?

1434
01:40:51,041 --> 01:40:54,753
Well, I really didn't know what to think.
I just knew that the man had been shot.

1435
01:40:55,170 --> 01:40:59,508
Did you think you might be shot dead
by the two cold-blooded killers?

1436
01:41:00,717 --> 01:41:02,052
Yes, I did.

1437
01:41:02,219 --> 01:41:06,390
Yet, despite that fear, despite
that risk to your life...

1438
01:41:06,598 --> 01:41:10,727
...you looked at their
faces as they left?

1439
01:41:11,478 --> 01:41:13,438
-Yes, I did.
-Is that correct?

1440
01:41:15,190 --> 01:41:15,857
Yes, I did.

1441
01:41:16,775 --> 01:41:18,944
Did you look at their faces?
Did you really...

1442
01:41:19,611 --> 01:41:22,948
...really look, Mrs. Salinas?

1443
01:41:23,365 --> 01:41:26,702
I glanced at them when they
walked by, but I did see them!

1444
01:41:27,077 --> 01:41:30,873
You... glanced?
You didn't look?

1445
01:41:32,040 --> 01:41:33,125
I saw them!

1446
01:41:34,334 --> 01:41:38,589
You glanced at them, Mrs. Salinas.
You glanced at them through the eyes...

1447
01:41:38,922 --> 01:41:43,594
...of a very frightened woman who
maybe had too much to drink.

1448
01:41:44,595 --> 01:41:47,222
-Objection, Your Honour.
-There is no need, Your Honour.

1449
01:41:47,347 --> 01:41:48,724
I have no further questions.

1450
01:41:48,932 --> 01:41:51,351
Thank you, Mrs. Salinas.
You may step down.

1451
01:41:55,272 --> 01:41:57,107
It was 6:15 on Sunday morning.

1452
01:41:57,316 --> 01:42:00,694
Frank Magicco worked out of
a homicide unit in Brooklyn.

1453
01:42:00,986 --> 01:42:03,989
He was a first grade detective with
an honest name and a solid reputation.

1454
01:42:04,656 --> 01:42:06,199
He was also King Benny's nephew.

1455
01:42:07,117 --> 01:42:09,161
Nick Davenport
was with Internal Affairs.

1456
01:42:10,120 --> 01:42:12,789
He was ambitious and wanted to make
captain before he hit forty.

1457
01:42:13,207 --> 01:42:15,459
He knew the fastest way up
the track was to reel in a...

1458
01:42:15,626 --> 01:42:18,378
...maximum amount of dirty cops
in a minimum amount of time.

1459
01:42:19,046 --> 01:42:20,380
Frank, what is this shit?

1460
01:42:20,881 --> 01:42:22,591
If I were you, I'd do what the kid says.

1461
01:42:23,342 --> 01:42:24,092
You make this one...

1462
01:42:24,176 --> 01:42:26,303
...you're gonna be having breakfast
once a month with the Commissioner.

1463
01:42:26,553 --> 01:42:29,973
You know, you got a real hard-on for this
Styler guy. What's your beef with him?

1464
01:42:30,140 --> 01:42:32,309
-One more thing.
-I can't wait.

1465
01:42:32,476 --> 01:42:37,147
It's simple. No one knows who fed you
this information. And I mean, nobody.

1466
01:42:37,481 --> 01:42:38,357
How did you get it?

1467
01:42:38,523 --> 01:42:41,860
It fell into my lap... just like
it's gonna fall into yours.

1468
01:42:49,159 --> 01:42:50,494
Christ Almighty!

1469
01:42:58,210 --> 01:42:59,586
You got everything in
here but a confession.

1470
01:42:59,753 --> 01:43:01,338
I thought I'd leave that up to you.

1471
01:43:01,713 --> 01:43:03,382
My preference is that
you beat it out of him.

1472
01:43:03,549 --> 01:43:05,050
There's even surveillance photos.

1473
01:43:05,926 --> 01:43:08,971
This piece of shit's pulling in about
five grand a month, ripping off pushers.

1474
01:43:09,054 --> 01:43:10,472
Has been for about 3 years.

1475
01:43:10,764 --> 01:43:12,683
-More like 4.
-He ain't gonna see 5.

1476
01:43:12,808 --> 01:43:14,184
So, you got enough for conviction?

1477
01:43:14,268 --> 01:43:16,395
That ain't up to me.
That's up to a jury.

1478
01:43:20,065 --> 01:43:21,400
Show the jury this.

1479
01:43:24,486 --> 01:43:25,487
What do you got there, Ness?

1480
01:43:25,904 --> 01:43:28,282
About 3 weeks ago,
the body of a drug dealer...

1481
01:43:28,448 --> 01:43:31,660
...named Indian Red Lopez was found
in an alley in Jackson Heights.

1482
01:43:32,244 --> 01:43:34,079
Three bullets in his head,
nothing in his pockets.

1483
01:43:34,162 --> 01:43:35,080
I'm with you so far.

1484
01:43:35,581 --> 01:43:38,000
This is the gun that killed him,
and these are the shells.

1485
01:43:38,667 --> 01:43:41,587
What's behind door number 3?

1486
01:43:42,296 --> 01:43:44,464
The prints on the gun
belong to Adam Styler.

1487
01:43:48,802 --> 01:43:50,804
-Hey, do me a favour, would you?
-What's that?

1488
01:43:50,971 --> 01:43:52,973
If I ever make it onto your
shit list, give me a call.

1489
01:43:54,057 --> 01:43:55,767
Give me a chance to apologise.

1490
01:43:56,685 --> 01:44:00,397
So, you need anything else, you talk to
Frank. He knows how to get a hold of me.

1491
01:44:00,772 --> 01:44:03,901
Take care of yourself, kid.
Water gets choppy out your way.

1492
01:44:04,318 --> 01:44:05,360
I'll do what I can.

1493
01:44:07,154 --> 01:44:10,490
Hey, Ness... did you ever
think of becoming a cop?

1494
01:44:11,658 --> 01:44:12,784
And leave the good guys?

1495
01:44:30,886 --> 01:44:32,221
The body of Christ.

1496
01:44:56,620 --> 01:44:57,788
The body of Christ.

1497
01:45:01,542 --> 01:45:03,544
Michael had done all
that could be expected...

1498
01:45:03,710 --> 01:45:06,547
...of an Assistant District Attorney
seeking a conviction.

1499
01:45:07,297 --> 01:45:11,552
He had a forensic expert detail the make
and caliber of the gun that killed Nokes.

1500
01:45:12,052 --> 01:45:14,471
He just never had the murder
weapon to present as evidence.

1501
01:45:14,638 --> 01:45:16,890
And he never gave the jury
a motive for the murder.

1502
01:45:18,767 --> 01:45:21,103
The tension of his task,
the hours he was working...

1503
01:45:21,186 --> 01:45:23,647
...and the uncertainty about
the outcome weighed heavily on him.

1504
01:45:24,064 --> 01:45:25,190
Did you see their faces?

1505
01:45:25,649 --> 01:45:28,443
Yes, I looked at them,
and they looked at me.

1506
01:45:28,569 --> 01:45:29,653
Did they say anything to you?

1507
01:45:29,903 --> 01:45:32,531
No, they just looked at me
and walked out of McHale's.

1508
01:45:32,698 --> 01:45:34,866
Are you sure the two
defendants killed Sean Nokes?

1509
01:45:35,033 --> 01:45:36,159
I know they killed him.

1510
01:45:36,869 --> 01:45:39,162
If the plan worked, it would
be everyone's success.

1511
01:45:39,872 --> 01:45:41,874
If it failed, the fault
would fall to Michael.

1512
01:45:45,377 --> 01:45:49,381
Father Bobby Carillo, the priest with
the best hook shot on the West Side...

1513
01:45:49,590 --> 01:45:53,176
...remained the key to a plan that called
for all involved to get away with murder.

1514
01:45:54,136 --> 01:45:57,472
Did you turn around, look behind you,
when you heard the shooting, Mr. Carson?

1515
01:45:57,723 --> 01:45:59,308
Why didn't you turn around, Mr. Carson?

1516
01:45:59,558 --> 01:46:02,394
I was concerned for my
companion's safety.

1517
01:46:02,561 --> 01:46:04,396
Mr. Carson, did the two individuals
threaten you in any way?

1518
01:46:05,564 --> 01:46:08,525
Did they threaten anyone
in McHale's Restaurant?

1519
01:46:10,360 --> 01:46:11,695
I didn't see it, but I know it!

1520
01:46:12,237 --> 01:46:14,531
If you didn't see the defendant
shoot the guard...

1521
01:46:14,615 --> 01:46:16,867
...then how do you know it was
the defendant that shot him?

1522
01:46:40,682 --> 01:46:41,850
So, what's the emergency?

1523
01:46:46,480 --> 01:46:48,273
Shakes shouldn't have sent you.
It's too risky.

1524
01:46:48,482 --> 01:46:51,818
Hey, nobody sent me.
I wanted to see you.

1525
01:46:53,820 --> 01:46:54,696
Why?

1526
01:46:56,406 --> 01:46:58,700
Shakes met with Father Bobby
2 weeks ago.

1527
01:46:59,368 --> 01:47:02,371
-He hasn't heard from him since.
-It's not an overnight decision for him.

1528
01:47:06,667 --> 01:47:09,670
-What if he doesn't testify?
-Then we got a very serious problem.

1529
01:47:25,769 --> 01:47:27,771
Have Shakes talk to Father Bobby again.

1530
01:47:29,523 --> 01:47:32,734
Have him tell him the whole story.
He'll know what that means.

1531
01:47:33,652 --> 01:47:34,778
He already has.

1532
01:47:36,363 --> 01:47:37,239
What!?

1533
01:47:38,574 --> 01:47:42,202
I... was with him when he
talked to Father Bobby.

1534
01:47:45,414 --> 01:47:46,957
I heard everything, Michael.

1535
01:47:57,175 --> 01:47:58,260
So, you know.

1536
01:48:06,518 --> 01:48:07,936
If only you told me.

1537
01:48:13,025 --> 01:48:14,818
I think things could've been different.

1538
01:48:17,529 --> 01:48:18,906
If you could've talked.

1539
01:48:24,119 --> 01:48:26,121
Maybe... maybe we...

1540
01:48:30,334 --> 01:48:31,293
Maybe...

1541
01:48:56,860 --> 01:48:59,279
Carmen, that diet is working.
I don't care what anybody says.

1542
01:49:01,907 --> 01:49:03,742
You still have a thing for Doris Day.

1543
01:49:04,201 --> 01:49:08,247
She was a good woman.
You know the strega?

1544
01:49:09,540 --> 01:49:12,000
It's hard to miss a lady with
four warts and only one eye.

1545
01:49:12,918 --> 01:49:15,212
She needs the heads.

1546
01:49:20,884 --> 01:49:22,219
Take this to the witch.

1547
01:49:23,929 --> 01:49:25,514
Now, why does she need that?

1548
01:49:25,639 --> 01:49:28,559
-She takes the eyes.
-Wonderful!

1549
01:49:28,767 --> 01:49:32,271
Puts them in a bowl and mixes
them with water and oil.

1550
01:49:32,813 --> 01:49:33,647
And then?

1551
01:49:35,732 --> 01:49:40,028
People get headaches, they go to her.
She looks into their eyes...

1552
01:49:40,237 --> 01:49:43,240
...and tells them who is
wishing the headaches.

1553
01:49:43,865 --> 01:49:47,411
She says a few words, and
the headaches go away.

1554
01:49:48,078 --> 01:49:52,416
Once in a while, the person who
wished the headaches, goes away too.

1555
01:49:53,250 --> 01:49:56,753
This guy, Addison, the one
who works for the Mayor...

1556
01:49:56,920 --> 01:49:59,047
...he quits his job in 2 weeks.

1557
01:50:00,257 --> 01:50:03,760
He don't want nobody to know
what kind of a guy he is.

1558
01:50:03,969 --> 01:50:07,139
He don't want nobody to see
pictures of him they shouldn't see.

1559
01:50:08,640 --> 01:50:10,225
-He knows this?
-He will.

1560
01:50:11,685 --> 01:50:14,479
The boys he buys for
parties are expensive.

1561
01:50:14,646 --> 01:50:17,983
Now, Addison makes good money,
but he don't make real money.

1562
01:50:19,318 --> 01:50:20,485
How much does he owe?

1563
01:50:20,652 --> 01:50:24,656
Eight grand with a heavy vig.
I paid that off.

1564
01:50:24,823 --> 01:50:29,119
-You paid?
-Addison's debts belong to me now.

1565
01:50:30,746 --> 01:50:33,248
-You hate debts.
-I hate Addison!

1566
01:50:36,043 --> 01:50:39,254
We're in the dirty end of the field now.
That's where I play.

1567
01:50:39,671 --> 01:50:41,381
And I like to play alone.

1568
01:50:42,049 --> 01:50:46,595
You're a nice kid. You always were.
Don't let this change it.

1569
01:50:59,900 --> 01:51:04,321
His mother named him Edward Goldenberg
Robinson, after her favourite actor.

1570
01:51:05,030 --> 01:51:06,365
To continue the Hollywood connection...

1571
01:51:06,406 --> 01:51:09,034
Eddie Robinson took the street name
"Little Caesar"...

1572
01:51:09,618 --> 01:51:12,538
...as he made his way up the ranks
of the lucrative drug trade.

1573
01:51:13,121 --> 01:51:16,250
He had a 12-year-old son in a
private school in upstate New York.

1574
01:51:17,084 --> 01:51:19,044
He named him Rizzo,
after his youngest brother...

1575
01:51:19,253 --> 01:51:22,673
...who died while in the custody
of the Wilkinson Home for Boys.

1576
01:51:23,423 --> 01:51:26,593
-I want you to give me some money.
-All right.

1577
01:51:27,135 --> 01:51:30,472
I'll play along.
How long before you pay it back?

1578
01:51:30,973 --> 01:51:34,309
I ain't paying it back.
Somebody else is.

1579
01:51:36,937 --> 01:51:38,272
This somebody I know?

1580
01:51:38,605 --> 01:51:41,942
-Your little brother knew him.
-Rizzo?

1581
01:51:44,695 --> 01:51:45,946
How did he know Rizzo?

1582
01:51:46,572 --> 01:51:50,993
Henry Addison was a guard
in an upstate reform school.

1583
01:51:51,285 --> 01:51:55,622
He was there the same time as Rizzo,
before and after he died.

1584
01:52:01,461 --> 01:52:04,006
Count out $8,000.
Put it in an envelope.

1585
01:52:08,010 --> 01:52:12,139
You... go back a long time, old man.

1586
01:52:13,557 --> 01:52:15,017
Old men always do.

1587
01:52:15,475 --> 01:52:18,270
Ran with the guineas, back
when the guineas were tough.

1588
01:52:18,312 --> 01:52:19,646
I ran when I could.

1589
01:52:20,898 --> 01:52:22,357
Looked good doing it, too.

1590
01:52:25,277 --> 01:52:29,281
Gave the business some style, some class.

1591
01:52:31,033 --> 01:52:34,036
Made it a call for respect, the way
you wore it... the way you talked it.

1592
01:52:35,662 --> 01:52:37,664
I always liked that about you.

1593
01:52:38,207 --> 01:52:41,543
I'm no help to you.
My tailor is dead.

1594
01:52:48,550 --> 01:52:52,888
I'll look up our friend and
collect the money he owes me.

1595
01:52:53,180 --> 01:52:55,182
He owes you something more than money.

1596
01:52:55,724 --> 01:52:57,643
Ain't nothing worth more than the green.

1597
01:52:58,143 --> 01:53:00,896
-This is.
-What, old man?

1598
01:53:01,897 --> 01:53:04,107
What's this guy owe that
means more than dollars?

1599
01:53:04,650 --> 01:53:08,612
He owes you Rizzo. He's the man
that killed your brother.

1600
01:53:17,829 --> 01:53:19,957
They said he died of pneumonia.

1601
01:53:20,916 --> 01:53:21,583
They said.

1602
01:53:28,924 --> 01:53:30,592
What is the relevance of this?

1603
01:53:31,093 --> 01:53:33,762
So, Ralph Ferguson is
a Sunday school teacher?

1604
01:53:33,971 --> 01:53:36,765
I don't know, counsel.
What you're asking is highly unusual.

1605
01:53:37,641 --> 01:53:41,812
I understand that, Your Honour. Again,
I need to put a face to the victim.

1606
01:53:42,980 --> 01:53:45,816
Otherwise it's just another
name in the obituaries.

1607
01:53:46,525 --> 01:53:48,610
Mr. Snyder, any objections?

1608
01:53:50,779 --> 01:53:52,072
I don't have a problem with that.

1609
01:53:53,365 --> 01:53:56,702
Your Honour, the prosecution would like
to call Ralph Ferguson to the stand.

1610
01:54:23,312 --> 01:54:25,397
-Good morning, Mr. Ferguson.
-Good morning.

1611
01:54:26,106 --> 01:54:29,026
I'd like to thank you for coming, I
understand it's been a long trip for you.

1612
01:54:29,985 --> 01:54:31,945
I'm just sorry it had to be
for something like this.

1613
01:54:33,405 --> 01:54:35,782
You and the victim, Sean Nokes,
were such good friends.

1614
01:54:35,949 --> 01:54:38,619
I think your testimony as a character
witness will be very valuable.

1615
01:54:38,869 --> 01:54:41,538
We were great friends. It would
be hard to find a better friend.

1616
01:54:42,331 --> 01:54:46,126
-Would you say you were his best friend?
-I was his closest, that's for sure.

1617
01:54:46,919 --> 01:54:50,881
-How long did you know each other?
-About 17, 18 years.

1618
01:54:51,673 --> 01:54:53,008
And did you see each other often?

1619
01:54:53,508 --> 01:54:57,930
As often as we could...
weekends, holidays, vacations.

1620
01:54:59,848 --> 01:55:03,435
-What kind of man was Sean Nokes?
-He was a good man.

1621
01:55:03,810 --> 01:55:06,021
He was too good to be shot dead
by a couple of street punks.

1622
01:55:06,647 --> 01:55:09,024
Objection, Your Honour, statement
is one of opinion not fact.

1623
01:55:09,274 --> 01:55:10,442
He was asked his opinion.

1624
01:55:10,651 --> 01:55:12,778
Overruled. Please proceed.

1625
01:55:14,529 --> 01:55:18,825
Mr. Ferguson... were you aware of
any enemies he might have had?

1626
01:55:19,201 --> 01:55:20,953
Sean Nokes had no enemies.

1627
01:55:21,703 --> 01:55:25,040
Thank you, Mr. Ferguson.
I have no further questions.

1628
01:55:29,795 --> 01:55:31,296
Is that a prison?

1629
01:55:31,463 --> 01:55:33,840
No, it's a juvenile
facility for young boys.

1630
01:55:33,924 --> 01:55:36,927
Your function was what at this facility?

1631
01:55:37,052 --> 01:55:38,804
Standard stuff.

1632
01:55:38,971 --> 01:55:43,058
Keep the boys in line, make sure
they got to classes on time...

1633
01:55:43,809 --> 01:55:46,311
Keep an eye out for trouble,
put them down for the night.

1634
01:55:47,396 --> 01:55:51,149
As guards, were you and
Mr. Nokes allowed to use force to...

1635
01:55:51,316 --> 01:55:53,318
...as you put it,
"keep the boys in line"?

1636
01:55:53,902 --> 01:55:55,904
What... what do you mean, force?

1637
01:55:56,071 --> 01:55:56,947
Were you allowed to hit them?

1638
01:55:59,199 --> 01:56:00,075
Of course not.

1639
01:56:00,409 --> 01:56:04,204
Were any of the boys hit by any of the
guards any time at the Wilkinson home?

1640
01:56:05,747 --> 01:56:08,709
I'm sure something like that
may have happened. It was a...

1641
01:56:09,376 --> 01:56:12,713
...big place, but it wasn't
the common practice.

1642
01:56:12,880 --> 01:56:14,214
Let's narrow the place down.

1643
01:56:14,381 --> 01:56:17,759
Did you or Mr. Nokes ever hit any
of the boys under your care...

1644
01:56:17,926 --> 01:56:20,387
...at the Wilkinson Home for Boys?

1645
01:56:28,145 --> 01:56:30,606
Would you like me to
repeat the question?

1646
01:56:30,814 --> 01:56:31,732
No.

1647
01:56:33,817 --> 01:56:35,944
Then answer it, please.
And remember, you're under oath.

1648
01:56:36,987 --> 01:56:40,073
A few of the boys who we considered
to be discipline problems...

1649
01:56:40,240 --> 01:56:42,242
...were hit on occasion.

1650
01:56:42,451 --> 01:56:43,952
And how were they hit?

1651
01:56:44,161 --> 01:56:45,996
-I don't know what you mean.
-A fist?

1652
01:56:46,496 --> 01:56:50,334
Open hand? Kick? Baton, maybe?

1653
01:56:51,043 --> 01:56:54,755
-Depends on what the situation called for.
-Who determined that situation?

1654
01:56:55,297 --> 01:56:56,173
The guard on the scene.

1655
01:56:56,924 --> 01:56:58,926
That's a lot of power to
have over a boy, isn't it?

1656
01:56:59,426 --> 01:57:03,013
-It came with the job, sir.
-Did torture come with the job?

1657
01:57:12,314 --> 01:57:14,775
Boys were tortured, weren't they,
Mr. Ferguson?

1658
